reviewText:
+ Character Progression system that will have you scratching your head until you decide what to pump exp into;
+ Silent Hill-esque atmosphere with chilling music and creepy sound effects;
+ Journal based story telling similar to the old school Silent Hill and Resident Evil games;
+ Clever use of items; (multifuntional keys that only work once, a consumable portable save item etc.)
+ Challenging combat scenarios;
+ Stat based dialogue/exploration options similar to old-school RPGs.

- The voice acting sounds fake;
- The story is a little cliche; (well delivered, but you've heard it a million times)
- No sanity system. (seriously, a Lovecraftian RPG without a sanity system? why?)

VERDICT: I know people have hang-ups about commercial RPG Maker Games, but this is a good one, especially if you are  a fan of survival horror games and old-school RPGs.
